\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{1}{3n-1} + \frac{1}{3n-2}- \frac{2}{3n}= \ln(3)
1+\frac{1}{2} -\frac{2}{3} + \frac{1}{4} + \frac{1}{5} - \frac{2}{6} +\frac{1}{7} + \frac{1}{8} - \frac{2}{9} \dotsb = \ln(3)
 \displaystyle \frac{1}{m+1} = \int^1_0 x^m dx
 \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \int^1_0 \left( x^{3n-2} + x^{3n-3} -2 x^{3n-1}\right) dx
 = \int^1_0 \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \left( x^{3n-2} + x^{3n-3} -2 x^{3n-1}\right) dx
= \int^1_0 \frac{ x+1-2x^2}{1-x^3} dx= \int^1_0 \frac{2x+1}{x^2+x+1} dx  = \log (x^2+x+1) \biggr|^1_0=\log 3.
